From: xdna-emu project
Subject: Make pcidrv::scan_devices virtual

The emulator's drv_emu subclass needs to override scan_devices() to inject
a synthetic device entry without requiring real PCI sysfs entries.  The
base class declares it non-virtual, so the override is silently ignored.

Apply from the XRT source root (xdna-driver/xrt/ or the XRT repo):
  git apply /path/to/xrt-pcidrv-virtual-scan.patch

--- a/src/runtime_src/core/pcie/linux/pcidrv.h
+++ b/src/runtime_src/core/pcie/linux/pcidrv.h
@@ -35,8 +35,10 @@ public:
   virtual std::string
   sysfs_dev_node_dir() const = 0;

-  // Scan system, find all supported devices and add them to the list
-  void
+  // Scan system, find all supported devices and add them to the list.
+  // Virtual to allow non-PCI backends (e.g., emulators) to inject
+  // synthetic devices without requiring sysfs entries.
+  virtual void
   scan_devices(std::vector<std::shared_ptr<dev>>& ready_list,
                std::vector<std::shared_ptr<dev>>& nonready_list) const;
 private:
